### Test Transactions API Endpoints
### Make sure to replace {token} with actual auth token and {baseUrl} with your API base URL

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3004/api
@token = your-auth-token-here

### 1. Create Revenue Transaction
POST {{baseUrl}}/accounting/transactions
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "type": "revenue",
  "amount": 50000,
  "description": "Milk sales revenue",
  "transaction_date": "2025-01-18"
}

### 2. Create Expense Transaction
POST {{baseUrl}}/accounting/transactions
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "type": "expense",
  "amount": 15000,
  "description": "Transportation costs",
  "transaction_date": "2025-01-18"
}

### 3. Create Revenue with specific account
POST {{baseUrl}}/accounting/transactions
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "type": "revenue",
  "amount": 75000,
  "description": "Product sales",
  "transaction_date": "2025-01-18",
  "account_id": "account-uuid-here"
}

### 4. Get All Transactions
GET {{baseUrl}}/accounting/transactions
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 5. Get Revenue Transactions Only
GET {{baseUrl}}/accounting/transactions?type=revenue
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 6. Get Expense Transactions Only
GET {{baseUrl}}/accounting/transactions?type=expense
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 7. Get Transactions with Date Range
GET {{baseUrl}}/accounting/transactions?date_from=2025-01-01&date_to=2025-01-31
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 8. Get Transactions with Limit
GET {{baseUrl}}/accounting/transactions?limit=10
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 9. Get Revenue Transactions in Date Range
GET {{baseUrl}}/accounting/transactions?type=revenue&date_from=2025-01-01&date_to=2025-01-31&limit=20
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

